    • downloadDelay

      public long downloadDelay()
      Gets the amount time (in seconds) to wait before downloading an update. If set to 24 hours (86400 seconds), and an update was released on Wednesday, June 1, 2022, at 12PM, it will not download this update before Thursday, June 2, 2022, at 12PM. When running a dev-build, however, this value is overridden to 0.
      Specified by:
      downloadDelay in interface IConfigLoader
